name: McLaren 650S GT3
description: The McLaren 650S GT3 is a GT3-class car with a 495 horsepower 3.8 litre twin turbo V8 engine.

name: Bentley Continental GT3
description: The Bentley Continental GT3 is a large-bodied lightweight GT3-class car with a 600 horsepower 4.0 litre twin turbo engine.

name: Callaway Corvette C7 GT3-R
description: The Callaway Corvette C7 GT3-R is a GT3-class car with a 600 horsepower 6.1 litre V8 engine.

name: Mercedes AMG GT3
description: The Mercedes AMG GT3 is a GT3-class car with a 550 horsepower 6.3 litre naturally aspirated V8 engine.

name: Radical RXC Turbo GT3
description: The Radical RXC Turbo GT3 is a stiff and light open-cockpit GT3-class car with a 500 horsepower Ford Ecoboost V6 3.5 litre twin turbo engine.

name: Formula E 2018 Car
description: Experience the Official 2018 Formula E car, using regen and power modes and featuring the 2018 Formula E team liveries.

name: Hong Kong E-Prix Track
description: Welcome to the Official 2017 HKT Hong Kong E-Prix track. Based around the Central Harbourfront, the tight and twisty 1.86km track provides a huge challenge against the backdrop of Hong Kong's iconic sights.

name: KartSim Rental Kart
description: The Rental Kart from KartSim.

name: KartSim X30 Kart
description: The Iame Senior X30 Kart from KartSim.

name: KartSim Buckmore Park International Circuit
description: The Buckmore Park International Circuit from KartSim.

name: KartSim Paul Fletcher International
description: The Paul Fletcher International track from KartSim.

name: KartSim Glan Y Gors
description: The Glan Y Gors track from KartSim.

name: Corvette C7.R
description: The Chevrolet Corvette C7.R built by Pratt & Miller and Chevrolet for competition in endurance racing has had numerous successes throughout the years including a famous photo-finish at the 2106 Rolex 24h of Daytona.

name: Porsche 911 RSR
description: Another iconic car from Porsche, the 911 RSR combines technology and history to create another classic sports car. The car is used in endurance in the GTE class all over the world.

name: BMW M8 GTE
description: The BMW M8 GTE competes in multiple endurance series, combining cutting-edge technology with sheer beauty to create a car that will set new benchmarks in endurance racing.

name: Norma M30 LMP3
description: The Norma M30 LMP3, developed over 18 months with innovation at the heart. Homologated to LMP3, the M30 boasts maximum efficiency, optimising performance.

name: Oreca 07 LMP2
description: The Oreca 07 LMP2, combining daring engineering and skilfull know-how. Winner of WEC 2017 P2 class and Le Mans 2017 and used by several of the leading endurance teams in the world.

name: Sebring International Raceway
description: Welcome to the official 2018 Sebring International Raceway track. Sporting three different track layouts and a special version that replicates all the details of the 12 hours of Sebring, this laser scanned track is our most accurate one to date!

name: Formula E Gen2 2019-2022 Car
description: The outstanding Formula E Gen2 car has been upgraded to include the 2022 liveries alongside those of 2021, 2020 and 2019! A complete redesign to the Gen1 cars, the Gen2 car features more power and longevity, boasting double the energy storage capacity of the Gen1 car, meaning it can complete a whole race without having to change car mid-race. With 250 kW of power, the Gen2 will accelerate from 0-100 km/h in 2.8 seconds and go on to a top speed of 280 km/h, as well as including support for 'attack mode'

name: McLaren 720S GT3
description: To bring one of their new incredible cars onto race tracks, McLaren developed the stunning 720S GT3. Modern design, impressive aerodynamics and years of experience in Motorsport should help this car to claim wins among several premier GT3 events in 2019.

name: BMW M6 GT3
description: From the very start, the BMW M6 GT3 hit the grids all over the motorsport world and proved the V8 concept to the German manufacturer. Leading several Endurance events in different series and also claiming the 2018 FIA GT Worldcup title, this car is a winner.

name: Porsche 911 GT3 R
description: It probably wouldn't be called motorsport if the iconic brand Porsche wouldn't be part of a class. The 911 GT3 R is once again a very balanced, race-proven car by the German manufacturer, reinforcing their image as being amongst the highest rated contenders of a series.

name: Audi R8 LMS GT3
description: Considered as one of the all-time favourites, this midship RWD car by Audi has been competing in GT3 since the beginning, winning significant races around the globe for a variety of teams. A demanding but rewarding choice.

name: Aston Martin Vantage GT3
description: The second generation of the Aston Martin Vantage GT3 is ready for some serious racing action. It will enter GT events in 2019 and beefs up the already stunning road version of the Vantage. With the prestige and expertise Aston Martin brings into racing, it's a challenger you always have to keep an eye on.

name: Imola
description: The Autodromo Enzo e Dino Ferrari di Imola, better known as Imola, has hosted both the Italian and San Marino Grand Prix 28 times in total. This rF2 track comes in four versions: the classic, dangerous 1972 layout surrounded by nearby barriers before te introduction of chicanes to reduce its high speed nature, the 1988 layout that introduced a few chicanes, the 2001 layout with further modifications and chicanes and finally, the current configuration fully adapted to modern standards but still retaining a lot of the unique challenges that made it famous.

name: Virginia International Raceway
description: Virginia International Raceway (commonly known as 'VIR') is a race track located in Alton, Virginia VIR is an incredibly beautiful and diverse racetrack allowing for numerous configurations, suiting all types of categories from small club cars to big GT and powerful prototypes.

name: Guapore
description: Autódromo Internacional de Guaporé is a motorsports circuit in Guaporé, a small city in southern Brazil. It is one of the oldest race tracks in the country and traditionally hosts a variety of different categories, ranging from Classic tintops, modern endurance prototypes to racing trucks.

name: Ibarra
description: The Autódromo Internacional de Yahuarcocha, is located in Ibarra, Ecuador. It´s unique layout flowing around and in between a lake, mountains and even a vulcan makes it an unique driving experience.

name: Formula Vee
description: This popular trainer formula car is heavily based on parts from the classic VW Beetle. Its open differential and swing axle rear suspension makes it a constant challenge and ideal tool to develop your driving skills.

name: MCR Sports 2000
description: The MCR S2000 is an incredibly nimble 500kg british prototype features an I4 Duratec engine, and is popular racer both for its driving fun as well as close wheel-to-wheel races.

name: MetalMoro AJR
description: The AJR is the latest high-performance prototype from Brazilian manufacturer Metalmoro. Capable matching the performance of a modern LMP2 car, this versatile prototype can be used with a range of different engines - the rF2 version features versions with Honda K20 I4 Turbo, Powertec V8, Chevrolet V8 and Judd V10.

name: MetalMoro MR18
description: The MR18 is a succesful mid-range endurance prototype from Brazilian manufacturer Metalmoro. It features a Honda K20 I4 Turbo engine.

name: Puma GTE
description: A sensation amongst brazilian car enthusiasts from the 70s, the GTE is a modified version of the VW Beetle, featuring the same mechanics of the brazilian Fusca with a lower, light weight fiberglass bodywork in an iconic design. The rFactor2 version is modelled after the original car and runs on radial tyres.

name: Puma P052
description: The P052 is a modern reimagination of the 70s brazilian classic, it retains many of the pure driving atributes that made the originals so popular in Brazil. The current prototype as modelled in rFactor2 runs with tuned MIVEC engine, 5-speed gearbox and slick tyres.

name: Monaco E-Prix Track
description: Introducing the awesome Monaco E-Prix 2019, the 1.765 km tight and twisty circuit is known for intense racing, with the Formula E version testing drivers to the max!

name: Le Mans 24h
description: Introducing the iconic Le Mans 24h for rFactor 2, meticulously recreated, the 2018 track is modelled with millimetre precision using the latest in laser scan technology. Nothing but the best for this epic track. What other sim to bring out its real potential than rFactor 2 with it's heritage with endurance multi-class racing.

name: Porsche 911 GT3 Cup
description: When it comes to the ultimate customer racecar, the Porsche 911 GT3 Cup is probably high on that list, if not even the leader as in so many races. Used not only in the Porsche Cups around the entire globe, but also in several other racing series including the all famous 24 Hours at the Nürburgring, this Weisssach-masterpiece is a one of a kind. A 3.8-Liter with six cylinders, of course in boxer setting, is pushing this racer in a blink of an eye through every tough corner.

name: BMW M2 CS Racing
description: The BMW M2 CS Racing car is based on the F87 M2, with 3.0L turbo engine producing 550Nm of torque and 350 horsepower. Being built specifically for track usage, it quickly accelerates out of corners and has an engine with a flat power curve from 5000rpm, up to almost 7000rpm. Mid-corner, the M2's well known agility is kept in check by a set of four 285mm wide slicks on 18 inch rims. This is a great car for competitive racing on any track, and it features all the adjustments needed to make it highly competitive.

name: KartSim Adria
description: Alongside the Adria International Raceway lies the Adria Karting Raceway, situated in beautiful Italy, just an hour south of Venice. Built in 2014, it is one of the most modern kart tracks, and hosts many international karting events. The track itself sports a nice looking combination of concrete and colored run-off areas and is just over 1.3 kilometers long.

name: KartSim Kristianstad
description: Located in the south of Sweden is the Kristianstad karting circuit, a 1.2 kilometer long track that was repaved and upgraded to meet the demands of a CIK grade-A circuit in 2012. The track has 16 corners, two chicanes, and a level difference of 6 meters vertically.

name: KartSim Alaharma
description: The Alaharma circuit, sometimes also called the Mika Salo Circuit as it was designed by the former racing driver of the same name, is one of the most beautiful outdoor karting tracks. Located in Finland in the beautiful town of Alahärmä on the banks of the river Lapuanjoki, the 1 kilometer long course winds down the river and has several corners that challenge even the most experienced drivers.

name: Circuit d'Azur
description: Between the beautiful sea, regal casinos and the lifestyle of the fast and famous, it's up to you to carve your name into the tarmac as a winner of this challenging street circuit!

name: Ferrari 488 GTE
description: The Ferrari 488 GTE is Maranellos choice for the world of endurance racing. Scoring 490 horsepower on the dyno, the 4 liter V8 engine features a bi-turbo setup to create even power across the entire band of revs. Plenty of power to compete for the top positions at the legendary 24 Hours of Le Mans. But power isn't everything when it comes to the Ferrari, a fully tricked out aero package makes sure that the airflow is helping the 488 GTE to build as much downforce as possible.

name: New York E-Prix Track
description: Red Hook at the Brooklyn Harbor hosted the double-header championship finale of the ABB FIA Formula E Season 17/18 as well as 18/19. With the Big Apple as backdrop, this ePrix easily goes onto the 'most iconic stops'-list of the championship. Take on the challenge, 2.32 km of pure street racing while enjoying a unique view of the Statue of Liberty, welcome to New York!

name: Berlin E-Prix Track
description: Take on the challenging 2020 Berlin E-Prix circuit, situated at Tempelhof airport, this 1.927 km track allows for great overtakes and intense action.

name: Radical SR3 XX
description: The SR3 XX is the evolution of the best-selling race car in the world, the SR3 which was first introduced in 2001. While the styling mostly remained untouched with just a few key elements setting the XX apart from its predecessor, underneath it's an all new track weapon. The first thing noticed by drivers as most prominent change is probably the new steering wheel, functioning basically as the HUB of the car and giving the driver access to all kind of new functionalities to access, evaluate and analyze data, helping to improve on track. The car is still powered by the 4th Gen RPE-Suzuki engine including a dry sump oil system as standard that is hooked up to a six-speed sequential gearbox with paddle shift and auto-blip function and a Quaife limited-slip differential.

name: Circuit de Spa-Francorchamps
description: Introducing the mighty Circuit de Spa-Francorchamps for rFactor 2. From La Source through to the Bus Stop Chicane, Spa-Francorchamps has been meticulously recreated using laser scan data, to bring one of the most exciting and accurate racing circuits to rFactor 2.

name: eX ZERO (2021)
description: The 1,000 hp eX ZERO is the first electric racing car specifically developed for esports racing and the RCCO World eX Championship. It has four-wheel drive and a power-to-weight ratio of 1:1. The eX ZERO reaches a top speed of over 380 km/h in the lowest drag configuration and is challenging to drive even for professional racing drivers. “eX” stands for “electric experimental” prototypes and “ZERO” for zero emissions.

name: Cadillac DPi-V.R
description: The Cadillac DPi-V.R represents the very finest in American endurance racing engineering, having taken the IMSA WeatherTech Sportscar Championship by storm since its debut in 2017. Four Daytona 24H wins, two drivers championships and one of the most stunning designs in modern IMSA racing. A true thoroughbred race car.

name: Corvette C8.R GTE
description: Replacing the venerable Corvette C7.R was never going to be an easy task for Chevrolet, however the new Pratt & Miller developed machine has immediately picked up the baton dropped by its predecessor and proceeded to firmly establish itself as a competitive force to be reckoned with in the IMSA WeatherTech SportsCar Championship. Utilising a mid-engine design for this first time, this is the Corvette you all know and love, just a little bit different.

name: Ligier JS P217 LMP2
description: French marque and Former Formula One race winning squad Ligier partner up with Onroak Engineering to produce an exceptionally efficient and competitive vehicle, one that competes with some success in national and international endurance racing events. Racing in the popular LMP2 category, the Ligier is both striking to look at, and a real test of driver behind the wheel.

name: Diriyah E-Prix Track
description: The Diriyah E-Prix is a 21 turn, 2.459km Formula E circuit located in the region of Diriyah, Saudi Arabia. Exceptionally fast and containing some of the most demanding corner sequences in modern Formula E, this is a track that offers both great racing and an exciting driving experience. Drivers need to push hard, strategically use their Attack Zone boost and avoid contact with the ever present walls in order to achieve a good result on this circuit.

name: Rome E-Prix Track
description: The Rome E-Prix offers the longest lap of the Formula E World Championship at 2.860 km in length. Comprising 21 turns and producing a lap time in the region of the mid 1 minutes 30's, the Circuito Cittadino dell'EUR is a tough and beautiful Formula E venue, one that should challenge and excite drivers in equal measure.

name: Autodromo Nazionale di Monza
description: The Autodromo Nazionale di Monza. The Temple of Speed. Home to the Italian Grand Prix, host to slipstream battles and high speed wheel to wheel action, at 5.793km in length and featuring just 11 corners Monza packs a massive punch within its relatively simple looking layout. As one of the key destinations for any major International racing series, rFactor 2 players can now take on the challenge for themselves with this latest 2021 laserscanned version of the Italian venue.

name: Formula Pro
description: The Formula Pro represents the absolute pinnacle of open wheel racing in rFactor 2. 800 hp and up to 2400 kg of downforce set to the tune of a roaring V10 engine, this is a car that will excite and inspire drivers to go faster, longer and harder than ever before. Featuring the latest technology such as the halo head protection system and DRS, plus four different tyre compounds – the Formula Pro is an incredible racing machine.

name: KartSim Iame KZ EU
description: Senior kart with a Iame 6 speed 125cc Gearbox Box Engine. This shifter model is used in official European and World Championships and forms the pinnacle of kart racing.

name: KartSim Iame Mini Cadet X30 EU
description: Kart model for young racers 8-13 years old. Features an Iame cadet water cooled 60 cc kart engine. This model is used by young racing drivers in the Iame Euro Series and in local National Championships.

name: KartSim Whilton Mill
description: Based in Daventry in Northamptonshire, this 1200m track is one of the UK Kart Racer’s go to tracks for testing and racing and appears on most national competition calendars.

name: KartSim Larkhall WSKC
description: Based in Scotland, this 1140m has recently undergone major refurbishment making it one of the premier kart tracks in the North of the UK.

name: KartSim Zuera
description: Based in Spain this 1700m track is one of Spain’s premier outdoor Karting facilities and often features on the FIA European Championship Calendar.

name: KartSim Wackersdorf
description: Based in Germany this 1222m track is one of Germany’s premier outdoor Karting facilities and often features on the FIA European Championship Calendar.

name: KartSim T4 Series
description: The Tillotson T4 Series, which debuted in the 2019 Motorsport Ireland Championship, is designed to introduce new drivers to the higher levels of karting in a cost-effective, easy-to-use manner. It is the ideal setup for clubs and local federations who want to expand the appeal of professional-level karting to the weekend racer or motorsport enthusiast. It features a European style racing chassis, our high-power, low-maintenance 225cc racing engine, and an easy to adjust HW carburetor to make racing fast, easy and competitive.

name: Ligier JS P320 LMP3
description: Winner of the LMP3 Title in IMSA WeatherTech SportsCar Championship and the three major US endurance events in 2021: 24 Hours of Daytona, 12 Hours of Sebring and Petit Le Mans - the LMP3 category within rFactor 2 is about to get a lot more exciting, with the introduction of the mighty Ligier JS P320.

name: BMW M4 GT3
description: Beginning development life at the start of 2020, the brand-new BMW M4 GT3 has been created to represent the very latest flagship GT racer of the Bavarian marque. Adding to our highly popular and ever expanding GT3 class within the simulation, the BMW M4 GT3 represents the pinnacle of closed top GT engineering.

name: INDYCAR - Dallara IR18
description: The very latest 2021 specification Dallara IR-18 INDYCAR is here, complete with all the teams, drivers and liveries of the 2021 NTT INDYCAR Series. 2.2 litre V-6, twin-turbocharged with upwards of 700 horsepower, high downforce and push-to-pass with in car driving adjustments, this series represents the finest of American automotive racing.

name: Daytona International Speedway
description: Arguably the premier International racing venue in North America, the Daytona International Speedway is steeped in history from its 60 years of active competition. From the daunting challenges presented by the 2.5 mile Speedway, to the 13 corners that make up the endurance road course, Daytona is an endurance racing classic.

name: Toyota Corolla
description: One of the most modern BTCC specification NGTC cars on the grid, the Corolla has already proven to be a very potent machine within the championship, and now the rFactor 2 car team have lavished their attention to detail on recreating this beautiful vehicle in all of its glory for rFactor 2. Relatively easy to drive once you reacquaint yourself with a front-wheel drive machine, but incredibly challenging to master, this is touring car racing at its very best.

name: Infiniti Q50 V37
description: The dominant car of recent years in the British Touring Car Championship, the Infiniti Q50 (V37) BTCC is an incredible representation of what rear-wheel drive modern touring car racing can be. Lovingly recreated in virtual form by the rFactor 2 team at Studio 397, this car is one of the best examples of touring car racing in virtual motorsport, and is sure to provide excitement and close racing action to anyone who takes it out onto the track.

name: Donington Park
description: At 2.498 miles (Grand Prix) and 1.957 miles (National) respectively, Donington Park is an exciting and challenging driver's circuit, with a healthy mix of fast flowing turns and technical sections. One of the most loved circuits in British national motorsport, and scene of the now infamous opening lap of the 1993 European Grand Prix, this is one track that is perfect for almost any type of virtual race machine.

name: Brands Hatch
description: Simply a spectacular venue to go racing in any weather conditions, Brands Hatch is one of the finest and most well known international circuits in Great Britain. With a rich legacy of history, this track has played host to countless iconic moments in motorsport, and with the introduction of both the Indy and Grand Prix layout in rFactor 2, now is the time to write your own chapter out on the virtual tarmac.

name: Laguna Seca
description: Is there a more iconic section of corners than the infamous 'Corkscrew' at Laguna Seca? Probably not, and now you can drive it for yourself in rFactor 2! Built on laserscan data and featuring all the bumps, twists, turns and undulations of the real thing, this track is one of those incredible driving experiences that encourage racers to keep coming back and try again for just one more lap - an outstanding experience.

name: Loch Drummond
description: Located just outside Stirling in the small vilage of Drummond, Scotland, is perhaps the home of the earliest known location of racing. Whether you consider it to be simple folklore, or to have some basis in reality, the valley has certainly held racing events since the 1950’s, but possibly for thousands of years. Based around what is assumed to be a disused and abandoned military installation, and surrounded by the walls of the valley, Loch Drummond is a relatively slow speed and highly technical track of two layouts (1.2 and 1.97 miles), that can really punish with lost time over a whole lap, for a mistake in a single corner.

name: World Wide Technology Raceway
description: A staple of the IndyCar schedule in oval form, Gateway is one of the lesser known circuits of American motorsport, yet something of a hidden gem in terms of how high speed and quite challenging the layout can be in both road course and oval configuration. Laser scanned and built to the highest levels of accuracy, this is a track that will no doubt surprise and delight in equal measure.

name: Ford Focus ST
description: The latest generation of racing Ford is here, in the form of the beautiful British Touring Car NGTC specification Ford Focus ST. One of the most prominent brands in the series, and a car that is more than proving up to the challenge of racing for overall victory, the Focus is an exceptionally well engineered piece of equipment, and in rFactor 2, this car is sure to get the pulse racing just as hard as the action on track.

name: Hyundai i30 Fastback N Performance
description: The Hyundai i30 Fastback N Performance is one of the most visually stunning cars in the current British Touring Car Championship field, and now you can sample all the thrills of racing this impressive touring car in rFactor 2. Featuring the team, liveries and drivers of the 2021/22 BTCC season, the Hyundai is a fantastic car in which to recreate the thrills of British Touring Car Championship Racing.

name: Austin Mini Cooper S MkI Group 2
description: The mighty Mini comes to rFactor 2. Featuring 24 period liveries and all the excitement that only a vintage Mk1 Group 2 Mini can produce, this small but potent race car is certain to set pulses racing when pushed hard on track - big things come in little packages.

name: Bahrain International Circuit
description: The Bahrain International Circuit comes to rFactor 2. Fully laserscanned and featuring four unique layouts - Grand Prix, Endurance, Outer Loop and Paddock - Bahrain is the perfect combination of high speed, technical and challenging corner types that offer a sensational experience across a wide range of different cars.

name: Thruxton Circuit
description: Thrilling Thruxton! The fastest circuit in British motorsport, Thruxton is not for the faint of heart. Developed with full laserscan technology and running to a total length of 3.791 km, this track is one of the most dramatic, difficult and high speed circuits in motorsport - a challenge for any car and any conditions.

name: Croft Circuit
description: Located in North Yorkshire and running to 3.423 km in length, the Croft circuit is a popular addition to British motorsport championships, hosting rounds of the British Touring Car Championship and Formula 4 amongst others. Recreated in full laserscan detail, this 16 turn challenging circuit is a perfect playground for a wide variety of car classes founds within rFactor 2.

name: London E-Prix
description: The latest in our line of laserscanned Formula E circuits is about to hit rFactor 2, as we proudly introduce the innovative and very different London E-Prix. The track features no less than 22 turns and runs to 2.252 km in length, including the unique indoor arena section that starts the lap - a very different, and challenging driving experience.

name: BMW 330i M Sport
description: The mighty BTCC BMW 330i M Sport arrives in rFactor 2. As one of the most potent cars in modern British Touring Car Championship history, having lifted Colin Turkington to the drivers crown on debut in 2019, the real wheel drive 330 M Sport is an incredible example of what a touring car machine can do - and it's available now in rFactor 2!

name: Vauxhall Astra
description: The venerable Astra is now coming to the end of its competitive lifecycle in the British Touring Car Championship, however despite its advancing years and lack of development in recent times, the car remains an exceptionally enjoyable front-wheel-drive racer, and one that remains very popular with fans of the sport - something we expect will transfer to the virtual version in rFactor 2. Shorter in wheelbase than many of the British Touring Car field, the Astra offers a different and more lively driving experience than most NGTC spec cars - something we think will be enjoyed a great deal by our community once you get used to the new driving experience.

name: Vanwall Vandervell LMH
description: The Vanwall Vandervell LMH sees a racing return for the famed Vanwall name, now run by established endurance outfit, ByKolles - and available in virtual form within rFactor 2! Built by the Vanwall team themselves, using extensive real world test data, this is the future of top level endurance sportscar racing!

name: Porsche GT3 Cup 992
description: Developed in conjunction with both Porsche themselves, and real world Porsche Cup driver and World's Fastest Gamer winner Rudy van Buren, the new Porsche GT3 Cup 992 is an incredibly exciting car on which to tackle the various race circuits available within rFactor 2. Producing a driving experience that is sure to keep drivers on their toes like only a Porsche Cup car can, this is a brutal yet engaging vehicle that offers up a little something for everyone - whilst making that stunning Porsche noise that we’ve all come to love in recent years. Built with supreme attention to detail - a lot of you have been waiting patiently for this one, and we are pretty sure you will all find it has been very much worth the wait!

name: Long Beach Grand Prix Street Circuit
description: As beautiful as it is difficult, Long Beach in California is a testament to ultimate driver skill and bravery - and now, in fully detailed laserscan form, you can try this stunning street circuit out for yourself in rFactor 2!

name: Honda Civic Type R
description: The mighty Honda Civic has proven to be one of the cars of choice in the British Touring Car Championship over the years, and now, you can get your hands on the very latest in the long line of tin-top Honda cars in rFactor 2, as we continue to expand our Touring Car offering within the simulation.

name: Formula E Gen3
description: The outstanding Formula E Gen3 car featuring all the liveries of Season 9 of the ABB FIA World Championship.  The Gen3 car features more power and longevity making it the fastest Formula E car yet with a top speed over 322 kph / 200 mph.  It features around 95% power efficiency from an electric motor delivering up to 350kW of power (470BHP), compared to approximately 40% for an internal combustion engine.

name: Cupra Leon
description: The ferocious Cupra Leon arrives in rFactor 2! After only entering the Championship in 2021, the Team HARD Cupra Leon’s have become a huge part of the grid - occupying 6 of the 27 total spaces. Get behind the wheel of your very own Cupra Leon now, and start tearing up the British countryside - only on rFactor 2!

name: GT3 Pack
description: GT racing its where it's at and with this bundle, you're ready to rock. Choose your favorite GT3 race car from the 14 available in this pack and dominate in the most diverse class out there: Aston Martin Vantage GT3, Audi R8 GT3 2018, Audi R8 GT3 2019, Bentley Continental GT3 2017, Bentley Continental GT3 2020, BMW M6 GT3, Callaway Corvette GT3-R, McLaren 650S GT3, McLaren 720S GT3, Mercedes AMG GT3, Porsche 911 GT3 R, Radical RXC Turbo GT3, Ferrari 488 GT3 Evo 2020 and the BMW M4 GT3.

name: Formula E Pack OLD
description: Motorsport is an ever-evolving story. Be at the front of it with this pack that is boosting you right into one of the most revolutionary FIA Championship out there. Recreate it's beginning with the Gen1 car or dive right into the current season with the Gen2 car and all original liveries, it's up to you which team you take around the 6 included original circuits: Monaco E-Prix, Berlin E-Prix, New York E-Prix, Hong Kong E-Prix, Rome E-Prix and Diriyah E-Prix.

name: KartSim Kart Pack
description: A great discounted package featuring all 5 of our consumer kart models.

name: Endurance Pack
description: If you're up for one of the biggest challenges in motorsport, this pack is for you. Get prepared for endurance races around the globe with 4 classes. No matter if Prototypes or GTs, it's in here: Cadillac DPi-V.R, McLaren Senna GTR, Ligier JS P217 LMP2, Oreca 07 LMP2, Norma M30 LMP3, Corvette C8.R GTE, Aston Martin Vantage GTE, BMW M8 GTE, Corvette C7.R, Porsche 911 RSR, Ferrari 488 GTE and the Ligier JS P320 LMP3.

name: Legendary Track Pack
description: Some tracks in the world of motorsport have a special status. They are icons, each representing a different kind of challenge but all being recognized as one of the toughest challenges out there. With this bundle, you can take on these adventures yourself. From the unforgiving Green Hell to the bumpy course around a former airfield, the playgrounds are waiting for you. Includes the Nürburgring, Le Mans, Sebring and the Circuit d'Azure.

name: Reiza Pack
description: The Reiza rFactor 2 Pack is here! This pack includes all Reiza content developed for rFactor 2: a total of 6 vehicles and 4 unique venues in 10 different layouts, mixing world-class race tracks such as Imola and VIR with exotic locations such as Ibarra and Guaporé; powerful modern prototypes such as the Metalmoro AJR with the challenging Formula Vee trainer. The Reiza rF2 Bundle combines the diverse content developed with quality standards and attention to detail Reiza became known for, with rFactor 2´s unique advanced simulation technology for a powerful sim racing experience!

name: Reiza Track Pack
description: The Reiza Track Pack includes Imola (1972 and 2018 versions), VIR 2018 in 5 different layouts, ecuadorian track Ibarra in 2 layouts as well as the Guaporé Autodrome from southern Brazil.

name: Reiza Car Pack
description: The Reiza Car Pack includes the Metalmoro AJR in 4 different engine configurations for 20 cars in total, Metalmoro MR18 in a 26-car field, Formula Vee in a 24-car field, MCR S2000 in a 20-car field, Puma GTE in a 10-car field; Puma P052 in a 20-car field.

name: GT3 Power Pack
description: Your final chance to purchase this bundle with some of the finest GT3 cars at a special discount! Featuring the McLaren 650S, Callaway Corvette, Mercedes AMG SLS, Radical RXC and Bentley Continental.

name: GT3 Challenger Pack
description: Your final chance to complete the collection with these five GT3 cars! Aston Martin Vantage, Porsche 911 GT3 R, McLaren 720S, BMW M6 and two different variations of the Audi R8 are waiting for you.

name: Two Strong Pack
description: Powerful engines, sophisticated suspensions and aerodynamics that let their work seem magical, that's what is needed to create a race car that can take on the world. Some might say there are even cars that are too strong – welcome to our Two Strong Package - featuring the Aston Martin Vantage GTE and the lightning fast McLaren Senna GTR!

name: KartSim European Track Pack
description: A great discounted package featuring all 5 of our consumer European Kart Tracks (Alaharma, Adria, Kristianstad, Zuera and Wackersdorf) and all of our 5 consumer kart models. Ideal for Esports competitions.

name: Daytona Pack
description: Celebrating American endurance motorsport, the Daytona Pack features the iconic Daytona International Speedway road and oval course, the mighty Ligier JS P320 LMP3 and the latest in German engineering, the BMW M4 GT3.

name: KartSim UK Track Pack
description: A great discounted package featuring all 5 of our consumer UK Kart Tracks (Larkhall, Whilton Mill, Paul Fletcher International, Buckmore Park and Glan Y Gors) and all 5 of our consumer kart models. Ideal for Esports competitions

name: KartSim Esports Pack
description: A great discounted package featuring all 10 of our consumer UK and European Kart Tracks (Larkhall, Whilton Mill, Paul Fletcher International, Buckmore Park, Glan Y Gors, Alaharma, Adria, Kristianstad, Zuera and Wackersdorf) and all of our 5 consumer kart models. Ideal for Esports competitions.

name: 2022 Q1 All In Pack
description: Four incredible pieces of content in one handy pack! Headlined by the Dallara INDYCAR IR-18, and featuring the world famous Daytona road and oval course, plus the addition of the BMW M4 GT3 and Ligier JS P320 – this is a great pack to enjoy some premium rFactor 2 content.

name: 2022 Q2 All In Pack
description: 3 iconic tracks and the best touring car racing has to offer - the full Q2 2022 content pack offers something for everyone. Laguna Seca, Donington Park, Brands Hatch plus the Infiniti Q50 and Toyota Corolla BTCC cars make a perfect collection of incredible sim racing content.

name: Touring Car Pack 1
description: Take to the racetracks in style with the Touring Car Pack for rFactor 2. Featuring two of the top touring cars in British motorsport, the Touring Car Pack contains the real wheel drive 2021 championship winning Infiniti Q50 (V37) and the front wheel driven Toyota Corolla BTCC, two cars that are sure to put a smile on your face when racing door-to-door, exactly as touring car racing should be!

name: Touring Car Pack
description: The front-wheel drive Toyota Corolla and rear driven Infiniti Q50 (V37) BTCC cars headline the Touring Car Pack, a perfect combination to join the laserscanned Donington Park and Brands Hatch circuits that make up an exceptional collection of content, ideal for close, hard and exciting racing action!

name: Best of The Best
description: Start your journey with some of our best content released so far!

name: Summmer Showdown Pack
description: Jump in to summer with the Showdown Pack, a great way to get to get to grips with some great content at a great price. Contains BMW M2 CS Racing, Bentley Continental GT3, Cadillac DPI-V.R, Corvette C7.R, Ligier JS P217 LMP2, McLaren Senna GTR., Porsche 911 GT3 Cup, Radical SR3 XX, Autodromo Nazionale di Monza, Imola and Virginia International Speedway. Available until July 7th 2022.

name: 2022 Q3 All In Pack
description: The full Q3 2022 DLC pack for rFactor 2. World Wide Technology Raceway, BTCC Hyundai i30 and Ford Focus plus the mighty vintage Mini - all designed to thrill and excite our community of racers.

name: Touring Car Pack 2
description: Containing two iconic NGTC specification British Touring Car Championship cars, the Hyundai i30 Fastback N Performance and Ford Focus ST, the BTCC Pack 2 is an ideal introduction into the high thrills world of touring car racing in rFactor 2. Featuring the official teams and liveries of the series, these two cars pack an awesome punch - ideal for some memorable racing moments on track.

name: IndyCar Pack
description: The IndyCar pack in rFactor 2. Featuring the stunning Dallara IR-18 plus laserscanned versions of Laguna Seca and Gateway, this is the best of American open wheel racing, right here in rFactor 2.

name: British Track Pack
description: The British Track Pack is here! Featuring high quality laserscanned versions of iconic British circuits Croft, Thruxton, Donington Park and Brands Hatch – this is the perfect way to discover incredibly exciting venues fit to host a variety of lively track adventures.

name: Formula E Pack
description: Motorsport is an ever-evolving story. Be at the front of it with this pack that is boosting you right into one of the most revolutionary FIA Championship out there. Recreate it's beginning with the Gen1 car or dive right into the current season with the Gen2 car and all original liveries, it's up to you which team you take around the 6 included original circuits: London E-Prix, Berlin E-Prix, New York E-Prix, Hong Kong E-Prix, Rome E-Prix and Diriyah E-Prix.

name: 2022 Q4 All In Pack
description: Featuring the best of Q4 2022 - the BMW 330i M Sport BTCC, the Vanwall Vandervell LMH and 4 outstanding, laserscanned circuits - Bahrain, Thruxton, Croft and ExCeL London Circuit.

name: LMVS 2022 Pack
description: The essential Le Mans Virtual Series Pack is here. Everything you need for the best online virtual endurance racing experience, just like in the Le Mans Virtual Series! 5 exceptional cars (Oreca 07, Ferrari, Porsche, BMW and Aston Martin GTE) plus the iconic locations of Sebring, Spa-Francorchamps, Monza, Bahrain and Le Mans - a super pack of exceptional racing content

name: 2022 The Complete Pack
description: The ultimate pack of 2022 is here - everything we've released in this calendar year, all in one convenient package. From IndyCar to BTCC and quite a few in between, a quality pack, with something for everyone.

name: 2023 Q1 All In Pack
description: The complete release pack for the first DLC drop of 2023. Feature a new car and track, this pack contains the BTCC specfification Honda Civic Type R, complete with all the teams, drivers and liveries of both the 2021 and 2022 British Touring Car Championship season, plus the fantastically detailed, laserscanned Long Beach Grand Prix Street Circuit - a premium set of content or rFactor 2.

name: Touring Car Pack 3
description: The third Touring car pack features three of the most interesting and competitive cars of the British Touring Car Championship. Rear wheel drive fans can look forward to the mighty BMW 330i, whilst those with an inclination towards front wheel drive have the superb little Vauxhall Astra, and the incredible Honda Civic Type R to enjoy.

name: Formula E Pack 2023
description: Motorsport is an ever-evolving story. Be at the front of it with this pack that is boosting you right into one of the most revolutionary FIA Championship out there. Recreate it's beginning with the Gen1, then dive into the Gen2 car, or if you are brave go straight into the current season with the stunning Gen3 car and all original liveries, it's up to you which team you take around the 6 included original circuits: London E-Prix, Berlin E-Prix, New York E-Prix, Hong Kong E-Prix, Rome E-Prix and Diriyah E-Prix.

name: Touring Car Complete Car Pack
description: Take to the track in style with the Touring Car Pack for rFactor 2! Featuring all 8 incredible Touring Cars and 3 seasons of stunning liveries, 2021-2023, our newest Touring Car Pack truly brings the Championship into the virtual world. The 8 thrilling cars included are as follows; Hyundai i30 Fastback N / BMW 330e M Sport / Ford Focus ST / Toyota Corolla GR Sport / Honda Civic Type R / Cupra Leon / Vauxhall Astra / Infiniti Q50.

name: Touring Car Total Pack
description: So, you like all things Touring Cars? Well, you’ve come to the right place! The Touring Car Total Pack in rFactor 2 is all-encompassing for a tin-top racing lover - featuring 8 incredible cars, 3 seasons of stunning liveries, and 4 of the greatest British racing circuits - Brands Hatch, Donington Park, Croft and Thruxton. What’s there not to love? The 8 thrilling cars included are as follows; Hyundai i30 Fastback N / BMW 330e M Sport / Ford Focus ST / Toyota Corolla GR Sport / Honda Civic Type R / Cupra Leon / Vauxhall Astra / Infiniti Q50.

name: GT3 Starter Pack
description: The ideal starter pack for GT3 racing! Choose your favorite GT3 race car from the 13 available in this pack and dominate in the most diverse class out there: Aston Martin Vantage GT3, Audi R8 GT3 2018, Audi R8 GT3 2019, Bentley Continental GT3 2017, Bentley Continental GT3 2020, BMW M6 GT3, Callaway Corvette GT3-R, McLaren 650S GT3, McLaren 720S GT3, Mercedes AMG GT3, Porsche 911 GT3 R, Radical RXC Turbo GT3 and the Ferrari 488 GT3 Evo 2020. Take them for a spin on two iconic tracks: Sebring International Raceway and Circuit de Spa-Francorchamps.

name: Formula Pro Pack
description: Three iconic and internationally renowned race circuits. One high performance modern open wheel race car. The Formula Pro Pack is the perfect collection of content to bring to you the speed and excitement of racing open wheel high performance cars within the rFactor 2. Designed specifically to get you competition ready for the new Formula Pro series, this is the perfect pack for high speed thrills. Buy, race, compete! The pack contains the Formula Pro, Circuit de Spa-Francorchamps, Nürburgring (and yes, that includes the famous Nordschleife) and the Autodromo Nazionale di Monza.

name: KartSim Upgrade Pack
description: If you had all our KartSim content before, this pack upgrades you with all the new content: 3 karts and 4 tracks (Zuera, Wackersdorf, Whilton Mill and Larkhall)

name: 5 minutes rFactor 2 Online server credit
description: Host your own races with friends or have a setup practice with your team with 5 mins of hosted server time through rFactor2 Online. Redeemable through game server menu

name: 1 Hour rFactor 2 Online server credit
description: Host your own races with friends or have a setup practice with your team with 60 mins (12x 5mins) of hosted server time through rFactor2 Online. Redeemable through game server menu.

name: 6 Hours rFactor 2 Online server credit
description: Host your own races with friends or have a setup practice with your team with 6 hours (72x 5mins) of hosted server time through rFactor2 Online. Redeemable through game server menu.

name: 12 Hours rFactor 2 Online server credit
description: Host your own races with friends or have a setup practice with your team with 12 hours (144x 5mins) of hosted server time through rFactor2 Online. Redeemable through game server menu.

name: 24 Hours rFactor 2 Online server credit
description: Host your own races with friends or have a setup practice with your team with 24 hours (288x 5mins) of hosted server time through rFactor2 Online. Redeemable through game server menu.

name: Complete Pack
description: Ever wanted to own every piece of rFactor 2 content released? Now you can. Including every DLC car & track* released and currently on sale, the rFactor 2 Complete Pack is the sim’s pinnacle. Check out all rFactor 2 content here - https://www.studio-397.com/cars-tracks/. *Pack does not include Reiza, KartSim or free workshop content

name: Total Car Pack
description: Complete your rFactor 2 content garage with the Total Car Pack. Including everything from Formula Pro, Classic Mini, BTCC, Prototypes, Formula E and Prototypes - rFactor 2 has machinery for everyone whatever your skill level and whatever discipline you enjoy.* Check out the full rFactor 2 car list - https://www.studio-397.com/cars-tracks/. *Pack does not include Reiza, KartSim or free workshop content.

name: Total Track Pack
description: Own and race on every track available now in rFactor 2*. From the classics including Nürburgring, Circuit de Spa-Francorchamps and Le Mans 24, to the streets of Long Beach & Rome, or British icons like Thruxton, Brands Hatch and Croft. Check out the full rFactor 2 track list here - https://www.studio-397.com/cars-tracks/. *Pack does not include Reiza, KartSim or free workshop content.

name: rF2 Online Intermediate Car Pack
description: Including all the content to compete in rFactor 2 Online Intermediate races, the Intermediate car pack has over 20 cars and some of the most recent cars to drop in rFactor 2. Race the hugely popular GT3 or BTCC cars, or battle it out in single make races with the 911 GT3 Cup (992) or BMW Class 1. Full list - Porsche 911 GT3 Cup (992), All BTCC (Hyundai i30 Fastback N / BMW 330e M Sport / Ford Focus ST / Toyota Corolla GR Sport / Honda Civic Type R / Cupra Leon / Vauxhall Astra / Infiniti Q50), LMP3 (Norma M30, Ligier JS P320), Austin Mini Cooper MKI Group 2, All GT3 (Aston Martin Vantage GT3, Audi R8 GT3 2018, Audi R8 GT3 2019, Bentley Continental GT3 2017, Bentley Continental GT3 2020, BMW M6 GT3, Callaway Corvette GT3-R, McLaren 650S GT3, McLaren 720S GT3, Mercedes AMG GT3, Porsche 911 GT3 R, Radical RXC Turbo GT3, Ferrari 488 GT3 Evo 2020 and the BMW M4 GT3)

name: rF2 Online Advanced Car Pack
description: This pack includes all the cars you need to compete in the ‘Advanced’ daily races. A compilation of all the most exciting and driver focussed cars in rFactor 2, from the pinnacle of GT cars to a high downforce, high horsepower single seater. Full list - Formula Gen3, Vanwall Vandervell LMH, INDYCAR Dallara IR-18, LMP2 (Oreca 07, Ligier JS P217), All GTE (Corvette C7.R, Corvette C8.R, BMW M8 GTE, Ferrari 488 GTE, Aston Martin Vantage GTE,  Porsche 911 RSR), Formula Pro
